-- SHADOW-SEMANTICS cell I6b (#669): the IMPORTER twin of d18 -- a value-position shadow
-- whose METHOD arity (2) DIFFERS from the imported STANDALONE's (1), UNANNOTATED.
--
-- Was a BUILD_CRASH (SEGFAULT) identical to d18: on the EMIT path the bare `size` was
-- typed as the permissive METHOD scheme (`a -> a -> Int`) rather than the imported
-- standalone (`Int -> Int`), because maybeStandaloneValueMono keys on the BARE name and
-- the mangler had renamed the imported standalone to `prov__size`.  So `map size [1,2,3]`
-- inferred element type `Int -> Int` (a function) and `println`'s
-- `Display (List (Int -> Int))` stamped a NULL element dict (RNone -> i64 0 word), and the
-- shipped binary dereferenced NULL -> SEGFAULT, while `run` was correct ([2, 3, 4])
-- because eval followed the RLocal route the same call had stamped.
--
-- ONE root cause with d18, ONE fix site: maybeStandaloneValueMonoEmit
-- (compiler/types/typecheck.mdk) recovers the post-mangle shadow from the occurrence's
-- RLocal route sym and pins the standalone scheme, grounding the element BEFORE
-- resolveDictApps.  standaloneSchemeFor resolves the importer here via the env under the
-- mangled sym (`prov__size`).  Exercised through the multi-module loader (this dir has
-- prov.mdk + main.mdk), NOT a single-file doctest, so the importer frame is real.
-- Expected: check accepts; run/build print [2, 3, 4].
import prov.{size}

data Box = Box Int

interface Sizeable a where
  size : a -> a -> Int

impl Sizeable Box where
  size (Box a) (Box b) = a + b

main = println (map size [1, 2, 3])
